\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cf1\insrsid286953 We remember when the Good Samaritan dressed the wounds of the man by the road. Sometimes a wound must be lanced - broken, in order for the pus to
 be drained, so that a healing balm may be added. So now we understand! We must be broken in order for us to heal.
\par  
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid286953 However, just as the body dreads being hurt, so does our pride resist being broken. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \cf1\lang1033\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid12717154 

